&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an early-stage startup seeking an experienced, creative, and AI-forward Marketing Manager to help grow and scale our marketing efforts. In this role, you’ll develop, test, and expand customer acquisition channels, with a strong emphasis on building scalable channels beyond paid advertising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be responsible for identifying new growth opportunities, experimenting quickly, improving campaign performance, and helping our product reach far and wide. With our product-led growth strategy, you’ll collaborate across teams to fuel customer acquisition, improve engagement, and expand our customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, onboard, evaluate, and optimize new marketing channels to drive significant lead volume within target customer acquisition costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale marketing channels from zero to meaningful reach, especially outside of paid channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools heavily to improve marketing workflows, accelerate experimentation, generate creative concepts, and scale campaign execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strong written content for ads, emails, landing pages, campaigns, and other marketing materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a library of creative concepts to communicate value to different buyer personas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve middle-of-funnel conversion rates through messaging and tactics that optimize customer engagement and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other departments to enhance creative quality and performance in digital marketing campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong startup experience and are comfortable working in a fast-moving, resourceful environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a heavy user of AI tools and know how to apply them to grow, automate, and scale marketing efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience scaling a marketing channel from zero to significant reach, ideally beyond paid acquisition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You love brainstorming new concepts, ad creatives, campaign ideas, and messaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience acquiring small businesses and prosumer customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You understand how to assess campaign impact and estimate the effort needed to generate results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can manage multiple projects simultaneously and identify the fastest path to value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You bring a full stack of marketing skills, from ideation to execution and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience managing paid digital marketing campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent command of the English language and are a strong writer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re able to create compelling content for ads, emails, landing pages, and campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a creative mindset and an eye for design, brand, and visual communication, and have used that ability to author copy, images, and videos with AI assistance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 3 years of marketing experience, including at least 1 year in a senior role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You Should Apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re passionate and skilled but don’t meet every qualification, please apply anyway. Talent, potential, and enthusiasm are highly valued here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;B12 is a safe and inclusive workplace, welcoming applicants from diverse backgrounds. We particularly encourage applications from women, people of color, underrepresented minorities, and members of the LGBTQIA community.&lt;/p&gt;
